OHM PAWAT CHITTSAWANGDEE

32
00:02:31,621 --> 00:02:34,151
NANI HIRUNKIT CHANGKHAM

33
00:02:34,381 --> 00:02:36,991
PHUWIN PHUWIN TANGSAKYUEN

34
00:02:37,221 --> 00:02:39,791
SATANG KITTIPHOP SEREEVICHAYASAWAT

35
00:02:39,901 --> 00:02:42,751
KAY KAY LERTSITTICHAI

36
00:02:42,981 --> 00:02:45,831
FILM RACHANUN MAHAWAN

37
00:02:46,061 --> 00:02:48,551
PIPLOY KANYARAT RUANGRUNG

38
00:03:10,661 --> 00:03:12,911
DIRECTED BY CHAINARONG TAMPONG

39
00:03:23,178 --> 00:03:25,936
(I think there's one thing I should let you know.)

40
00:03:26,028 --> 00:03:27,714
From now on, you must be careful

41
00:03:27,738 --> 00:03:31,609
when you meet someone new or make new friends

42
00:03:32,801 --> 00:03:34,404
because I'm not sure anymore

43
00:03:34,413 --> 00:03:36,006
what else our family will be facing.

44
00:03:37,623 --> 00:03:38,397
What do we do?

45
00:03:38,597 --> 00:03:39,520
I think we should do this.

46
00:03:39,530 --> 00:03:40,317
Let's do this.

47
00:03:47,263 --> 00:03:48,080
1

48
00:03:49,221 --> 00:03:49,751
2

49
00:03:49,764 --> 00:03:50,501
Let's go.

50
00:03:59,501 --> 00:04:00,363
You.

51
00:04:01,509 --> 00:04:02,701
What was your name?

52
00:04:03,069 --> 00:04:03,809
Mac.

53
00:04:03,923 --> 00:04:04,807
Right.

54
00:04:05,098 --> 00:04:06,358
What are you doing here?

55
00:04:07,909 --> 00:04:08,954
Well,

56
00:04:08,966 --> 00:04:10,361
just like Kong said last night.

57
00:04:10,763 --> 00:04:12,902
We can do anything here. We can come here anytime.

58
00:04:15,385 --> 00:04:16,183
Is that so?

59
00:04:17,105 --> 00:04:19,213
You can just drop Kong some messages.

60
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,517
Well, the thing is

61
00:04:21,936 --> 00:04:23,517
I actually said that last night.

62
00:04:24,779 --> 00:04:25,518
But...

63
00:04:28,909 --> 00:04:30,721
Last night when I came back,

64
00:04:30,957 --> 00:04:32,404
it was already messed up like this.

65
00:04:33,477 --> 00:04:35,308
Is there anything valuable?

66
00:04:36,604 --> 00:04:37,381
Should we call the cops?

67
00:04:37,403 --> 00:04:39,406
Hey, are you out of your mind?

68
00:04:39,868 --> 00:04:42,720
Are you going to call the cops on me and you for partying last night?

69
00:04:43,231 --> 00:04:44,004
It's fine.

70
00:04:44,015 --> 00:04:45,514
I didn't leave anything valuable.

71
00:04:48,302 --> 00:04:49,607
Then

72
00:04:49,866 --> 00:04:51,312
I'll help you clean it up.

73
00:04:51,579 --> 00:04:53,404
To make up for staying the night here last night.

74
00:04:54,306 --> 00:04:55,903
Let's do it together.

75
00:04:56,329 --> 00:04:58,201
We partied together so we should clean up together.

76
00:05:00,253 --> 00:05:02,505
I apologize for what happened last night.

77
00:05:04,151 --> 00:05:07,109
Actually, I think I should apologize to everyone.

78
00:05:12,683 --> 00:05:15,506
Don't you think Mac is a little strange?

79
00:05:16,423 --> 00:05:17,606
How so?

80
00:05:17,972 --> 00:05:19,505
Are you overthinking it?

81
00:05:20,028 --> 00:05:21,901
I'm just questioning.

82
00:05:22,638 --> 00:05:23,901
Well then,

83
00:05:24,215 --> 00:05:27,106
are you going to go to everyone and apologize?

84
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:28,683
- Yeah.
- Damn, such a nice guy.

85
00:05:28,702 --> 00:05:30,240
Isn't that the right thing to do?

86
00:05:30,412 --> 00:05:32,376
We invited them and they had to go through something like this.

87
00:05:32,392 --> 00:05:33,880
No one would be okay with that.

88
00:05:34,521 --> 00:05:37,301
But I think I like those people who stayed behind last night.

89
00:05:38,121 --> 00:05:40,401
I think they're the selected ones.

90
00:05:40,651 --> 00:05:43,801
They have that devil look in their eyes.

91
00:05:46,108 --> 00:05:47,803
We got into trouble right from the very first day.

92
00:05:57,566 --> 00:05:58,975
I think you can go alone, Kong.

93
00:05:58,992 --> 00:05:59,889
See you later.

94
00:05:59,899 --> 00:06:00,663
Hold on.

95
00:06:00,674 --> 00:06:02,037
Are you just going to ditch me?

96
00:06:02,221 --> 00:06:03,609
Yeah, can't help it.

97
00:06:04,388 --> 00:06:06,278
I have someone I should apologize to as well.

98
00:06:06,527 --> 00:06:07,767
Let's each get our redemptions done.

99
00:06:07,782 --> 00:06:08,618
See you, dude.

100
00:06:17,861 --> 00:06:21,031
(Tam's house)

101
00:06:21,141 --> 00:06:23,431
(Kong: I'm here.)

102
00:06:35,893 --> 00:06:36,709
What's wrong?

103
00:06:37,061 --> 00:06:38,606
Are you disappointed that it's me?

104
00:06:40,416 --> 00:06:41,302
No.

105
00:06:41,914 --> 00:06:43,809
I just didn't think you would be here too.

106
00:06:46,161 --> 00:06:47,606
That's because my guess was correct.

107
00:06:47,957 --> 00:06:50,118
If you're going to drop by someone's,

108
00:06:50,761 --> 00:06:52,111
the first one would be Tam.

109
00:06:54,142 --> 00:06:55,003
How's that?

110
00:06:55,169 --> 00:06:56,578
Don't I know exactly what you think?

111
00:07:09,352 --> 00:07:10,308
Kanya.

112
00:07:18,429 --> 00:07:19,401
Kanya.

113
00:07:31,277 --> 00:07:32,902
This is my grandma.

114
00:07:34,858 --> 00:07:37,204
So this is the friend you met up with yesterday?

115
00:07:41,308 --> 00:07:43,386
This is Kong and May.

116
00:07:43,410 --> 00:07:45,406
They go to the same faculty as I do, Grandma.

117
00:07:48,651 --> 00:07:49,388
Actually

118
00:07:49,401 --> 00:07:52,216
Actually, I have something to apologize for.

119
00:07:52,226 --> 00:07:54,216
It was so much fun, grandma.

120
00:07:54,426 --> 00:07:56,981
I met a lot of people yesterday.

121
00:07:58,089 --> 00:07:58,981
Right?

122
00:08:00,598 --> 00:08:01,406
Oh, yes.

123
00:08:01,623 --> 00:08:02,506
That's right.

124
00:08:03,493 --> 00:08:04,881
Community work.

125
00:08:05,342 --> 00:08:08,735
I still want to apologize

126
00:08:08,754 --> 00:08:09,969
for having a little too much fun.

127
00:08:09,978 --> 00:08:11,358
That doesn't sound quite decent

128
00:08:11,370 --> 00:08:13,152
the "little too much fun" part.

129
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:16,880
and a friend who's a man.

130
00:08:17,551 --> 00:08:20,503
Men and women can never be friends.

131
00:08:26,982 --> 00:08:27,812
Kanya.

132
00:08:28,561 --> 00:08:29,812
Kanya, please.

133
00:08:30,075 --> 00:08:33,518
Can't we even say hi or talk when we meet like other people do?

134
00:08:34,192 --> 00:08:36,152
I want this to end.

135
00:08:36,418 --> 00:08:38,204
I don't want any more trouble with my mom.

136
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:41,518
But we don't hate each other, do we, Kanya?

137
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:45,109
We haven't talked ever since.

138
00:08:47,853 --> 00:08:50,705
Maybe this is how we're supposed to part.

139
00:08:52,923 --> 00:08:54,506
We should never meet again.

140
00:08:54,893 --> 00:08:56,308
So we wouldn't get hurt again.

141
00:08:56,841 --> 00:08:58,406
Kanya, please.

142
00:08:59,032 --> 00:09:00,401
Do we have to go that far?

143
00:09:03,265 --> 00:09:04,535
It's better this way.

144
00:09:04,551 --> 00:09:05,994
I've made up my mind.

145
00:09:06,032 --> 00:09:07,009
Kanya

146
00:09:07,335 --> 00:09:08,506
Don't be like this, Kanya.

147
00:09:08,852 --> 00:09:09,415
Kanya.

148
00:09:09,426 --> 00:09:10,471
Help!

149
00:09:10,484 --> 00:09:11,615
- What's going on?
- Kanya!

150
00:09:11,718 --> 00:09:12,071
Kanya!

151
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,311
Sir, stop.

152
00:09:13,869 --> 00:09:15,013
What are you trying to do?

153
00:09:15,035 --> 00:09:17,312
Can't we even be friends?

154
00:09:18,370 --> 00:09:21,404
They can, actually, if they don't think of each other that way.

155
00:09:26,626 --> 00:09:28,609
You guys are still young, what do you know?

156
00:09:29,406 --> 00:09:31,108
Next time,

157
00:09:31,643 --> 00:09:33,361
if you're going to come over to this house,

158
00:09:34,369 --> 00:09:36,512
you have to get my permission first.

159
00:09:36,915 --> 00:09:37,607
Yes.

160
00:09:37,625 --> 00:09:38,809
Female friends only.

161
00:09:39,743 --> 00:09:41,105
A man shouldn't come anymore.

162
00:09:43,301 --> 00:09:44,804
And don't even think of hitting on her.

163
00:09:45,013 --> 00:09:46,379
Tam is allowed to have a boyfriend

164
00:09:46,389 --> 00:09:48,407
only when she's finished school.

165
00:10:05,813 --> 00:10:06,610
Oh?

166
00:10:08,847 --> 00:10:12,120
Don't ever let my grandma know where I've been last night.

167
00:10:12,972 --> 00:10:15,201
Even better if you pretend nothing happened.

168
00:10:16,703 --> 00:10:18,238
Are you living in jail?

169
00:10:19,465 --> 00:10:21,101
This is how things go in my house.

170
00:10:21,415 --> 00:10:22,702
Please understand.

171
00:10:23,986 --> 00:10:24,803
Yeah.

172
00:10:25,570 --> 00:10:29,351
Then you can't come to see Peem's audition tonight.

173
00:10:29,637 --> 00:10:30,409
Oh?

174
00:10:30,899 --> 00:10:32,001
Really?

175
00:10:33,373 --> 00:10:35,077
I thought we would get to go together.

176
00:10:36,068 --> 00:10:37,601
I don't want to get into trouble.

177
00:10:37,978 --> 00:10:39,081
Have fun on my behalf.

178
00:10:40,363 --> 00:10:41,401
What a shame.

179
00:10:46,861 --> 00:10:49,305
But it's good that Tam doesn't go, Kong.

180
00:10:49,609 --> 00:10:50,948
You see what her grandma's like.

181
00:10:50,961 --> 00:10:52,715
She wouldn't have it.

182
00:10:53,884 --> 00:10:55,603
Do you want Tam to get scolded even more?

183
00:10:58,161 --> 00:10:59,080
By the way, Kong.

184
00:10:59,692 --> 00:11:01,404
Please tell Pali.

185
00:11:01,661 --> 00:11:03,404
I don't think I can go tonight.

186
00:11:06,061 --> 00:11:07,078
He invited you already?

187
00:11:09,412 --> 00:11:10,204
Yeah.

188
00:11:10,683 --> 00:11:13,401
Pali was the one who took me home last night.

189
00:11:16,209 --> 00:11:17,078
Yeah.

190
00:11:36,941 --> 00:11:41,031
(Kong: Where are you, Pali?)

191
00:11:42,395 --> 00:11:48,609
Can we fall in love after a glimpse of each other's eyes?

192
00:11:49,044 --> 00:11:55,200
How can people's hearts be bonded within a split of a second?

193
00:11:57,386 --> 00:11:59,502
The game we played at the club that night was quite fun.

194
00:11:59,927 --> 00:12:01,692
We could just ask anything.

195
00:12:02,234 --> 00:12:03,401
Will I get to play it again today?

196
00:12:04,708 --> 00:12:06,306
You can just ask even if we're not playing a game.

197
00:12:06,487 --> 00:12:07,062
Why?

198
00:12:07,077 --> 00:12:08,006
What do you want to know?

199
00:12:11,881 --> 00:12:12,972
What about...

200
00:12:13,403 --> 00:12:15,398
Are you seeing or talking to anyone?

201
00:12:16,238 --> 00:12:17,105
Well.

202
00:12:17,672 --> 00:12:20,308
This question is even tougher than playing a game.

203
00:12:20,850 --> 00:12:21,601
Why?

204
00:12:21,755 --> 00:12:22,912
Is it a secret?

205
00:12:23,355 --> 00:12:25,278
No, I'm not seeing anyone.

206
00:12:25,600 --> 00:12:27,278
But I think I do want someone.

207
00:12:29,142 --> 00:12:30,403
What kind of person do you like?

208
00:12:32,662 --> 00:12:33,314
Umm..

209
00:12:33,326 --> 00:12:34,508
Well, I

210
00:12:35,366 --> 00:12:37,306
I probably like a kind girl.

211
00:12:37,806 --> 00:12:39,303
I think I have a soft spot for something like that.

212
00:12:42,591 --> 00:12:44,902
Having a girl ask me like this is a little embarrassing.

213
00:12:45,924 --> 00:12:47,127
Why are you embarrassed?

214
00:12:47,146 --> 00:12:48,515
You're just telling me your type.

215
00:12:49,941 --> 00:12:52,361
There are many more things to be embarrassed.

216
00:12:54,428 --> 00:12:57,634
You make me want to dive deep

217
00:12:57,644 --> 00:13:01,348
You make me want to have you in my sight

218
00:13:01,364 --> 00:13:04,563
You make me get lost in a land

219
00:13:04,592 --> 00:13:08,509
Too far to be found

220
00:13:09,003 --> 00:13:14,828
And no matter how near or far

221
00:13:15,472 --> 00:13:23,809
I will make it into your universe

222
00:13:36,065 --> 00:13:37,155
Thanks for coming.

223
00:13:37,813 --> 00:13:40,007
And thanks for letting me live with you.

224
00:14:12,101 --> 00:14:14,521
(May: If you don't have enough money for rent,)

225
00:14:14,533 --> 00:14:16,031
(Why don't we share a room?)

226
00:14:20,561 --> 00:14:21,615
Pardon me

227
00:14:22,179 --> 00:14:24,201
Is it okay if I speak colloquially with you?

228
00:14:25,606 --> 00:14:27,001
Do whatever you want.

229
00:14:29,714 --> 00:14:31,001
I'm really not bothering you, am I?

230
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:33,001
I don't look like a homeless, right?

231
00:14:35,720 --> 00:14:37,308
I just want a roommate.

232
00:14:37,628 --> 00:14:39,588
And you're not there to be my boyfriend.

233
00:14:39,612 --> 00:14:41,588
So there's nothing bothersome about it.

234
00:14:41,903 --> 00:14:42,709
Okay?

235
00:14:44,875 --> 00:14:45,637
Sure.

236
00:14:45,653 --> 00:14:49,038
I will return the best favor to make it worth your generosity.

237
00:14:49,858 --> 00:14:51,509
Do you even know what I want?

238
00:14:53,102 --> 00:14:54,881
I can tell even when I was on stage.

239
00:14:54,909 --> 00:14:56,881
You almost ate Kong up alive.

240
00:15:00,735 --> 00:15:02,007
Then...

241
00:15:02,621 --> 00:15:04,409
I think I should learn to hide it better.

242
00:15:05,247 --> 00:15:06,409
Just keep on doing it this way.

243
00:15:06,509 --> 00:15:07,441
Just keep going.

244
00:15:08,046 --> 00:15:09,281
I'll help you.

245
00:15:09,672 --> 00:15:10,983
It's all clear as well.

246
00:15:11,385 --> 00:15:12,803
Tam's not here.

247
00:15:13,840 --> 00:15:15,201
You noticed that too?

248
00:15:16,794 --> 00:15:20,303
The way Kong looks at Tam is just like how you look at Kong.

249
00:15:21,333 --> 00:15:24,102
When people like you are interested in someone,

250
00:15:24,957 --> 00:15:26,102
it's really easy to tell.

251
00:15:28,818 --> 00:15:30,803
Should I compliment you for being smart,

252
00:15:31,663 --> 00:15:33,701
or should I condemn you for being so nosy?

253
00:15:35,529 --> 00:15:36,508
I'm sorry.

254
00:15:36,788 --> 00:15:38,263
I just like to observe people.

255
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:39,198
It's fine.

256
00:15:40,228 --> 00:15:40,958
I like it.

257
00:15:42,253 --> 00:15:44,409
People aren't usually nice to me.

258
00:15:45,093 --> 00:15:46,701
They usually want something out of me.

259
00:15:47,447 --> 00:15:49,443
But it doesn't matter what you think of me.

260
00:15:49,994 --> 00:15:51,443
Rest assured.

261
00:15:51,538 --> 00:15:53,103
If you're sincere to me,

262
00:15:53,539 --> 00:15:55,080
I'll be sure to repay you nicely.

263
00:16:18,167 --> 00:16:19,404
Shop owner: You smoke?

264
00:16:20,691 --> 00:16:22,308
I carry it around for rainy days.

265
00:16:24,189 --> 00:16:25,317
Just like now.

266
00:16:29,052 --> 00:16:30,758
Should I wire it to your account or your phone number?

267
00:16:32,933 --> 00:16:33,952
Shop owner: What for?

268
00:16:36,013 --> 00:16:38,606
For having my friend sing here.

269
00:16:44,132 --> 00:16:44,909
Hey!

270
00:16:44,939 --> 00:16:46,329
I tried sneaking out.

271
00:16:46,336 --> 00:16:47,315
It was so exciting.

272
00:16:47,649 --> 00:16:49,807
Hey! That's so cool.

273
00:16:49,998 --> 00:16:50,672
Seriously though,

274
00:16:50,687 --> 00:16:52,705
I never thought I would see you here.

275
00:16:59,342 --> 00:17:01,358
By the way, where's Pali?

276
00:17:17,709 --> 00:17:18,803
May I drink with you?

277
00:17:31,049 --> 00:17:33,320
Why are you standing here all alone?

278
00:17:34,108 --> 00:17:36,207
