565
00:35:13,905 --> 00:35:18,111
You must be very good at relationships.

566
00:35:29,351 --> 00:35:31,120
What's up, you girls?

567
00:35:31,281 --> 00:35:32,253
Where have you been?

568
00:35:32,512 --> 00:35:33,733
None of your business.

569
00:35:37,409 --> 00:35:38,643
I think we've found her.

570
00:35:38,923 --> 00:35:40,472
The scissor mouth of the group.

571
00:35:40,483 --> 00:35:41,594
It's probably May.

572
00:35:43,203 --> 00:35:44,598
What are you guys doing?

573
00:35:45,038 --> 00:35:47,709
We're putting our heads together on what we should do.

574
00:35:48,111 --> 00:35:49,701
We're thinking about doing something fun.

575
00:35:51,758 --> 00:35:53,009
What on earth are you doing?

576
00:35:54,903 --> 00:35:55,972
Are you stealing?

577
00:35:55,982 --> 00:35:57,403
This is meant to be shared.

578
00:35:59,191 --> 00:35:59,933
Hey.

579
00:36:00,241 --> 00:36:01,409
I told Kong already.

580
00:36:02,041 --> 00:36:03,301
I want to bring it to my mum.

581
00:36:03,511 --> 00:36:04,561
She loves it.

582
00:36:05,238 --> 00:36:06,410
What the hell?

583
00:36:21,659 --> 00:36:22,960
Don't forget to bring this home.

584
00:36:24,520 --> 00:36:25,407
Thank you, sir.

585
00:36:27,295 --> 00:36:28,006
Oh?

586
00:36:28,163 --> 00:36:29,521
Are you hiding something from us?

587
00:36:30,078 --> 00:36:32,102
The hell are you saying, Peem?

588
00:36:37,978 --> 00:36:38,801
Is this yours?

589
00:36:39,339 --> 00:36:40,401
Tam gave it to me.

590
00:36:46,183 --> 00:36:48,006
Just say it.

591
00:36:48,597 --> 00:36:50,103
Don't make it such a big deal.

592
00:36:55,129 --> 00:36:55,905
Right.

593
00:36:57,856 --> 00:36:58,878
I think

594
00:36:59,843 --> 00:37:01,406
Tam and I have decided on it.

595
00:37:14,157 --> 00:37:15,803
I don't care

596
00:37:16,371 --> 00:37:18,105
if it's me who initiates it.

597
00:37:19,209 --> 00:37:21,109
But if you're not seeing anyone

598
00:37:22,791 --> 00:37:24,601
and I'm not seeing anyone,

599
00:37:29,989 --> 00:37:33,806
why don't we get to know each other better?

600
00:37:43,699 --> 00:37:45,040
Tam and I have decided.

601
00:37:45,789 --> 00:37:47,431
We're going to try learning more about each other.

602
00:37:55,226 --> 00:37:57,600
You guys are breaking the first rule so soon.

603
00:37:58,619 --> 00:37:59,905
I'm sure this will be fun.

604
00:38:08,561 --> 00:38:09,680
Why's Kong upset?

605
00:38:16,701 --> 00:38:19,440
Why do you always walk out on problems?

606
00:38:19,695 --> 00:38:21,441
Why are you taking the rules so seriously?

607
00:38:23,063 --> 00:38:24,812
I don't really care about the damn rule.

608
00:38:25,323 --> 00:38:26,308
But you...

609
00:38:26,698 --> 00:38:28,508
why don't you tell me when there's something up?

610
00:38:29,975 --> 00:38:31,440
I thought we were close.

611
00:38:32,483 --> 00:38:33,440
Oh.

612
00:38:35,395 --> 00:38:36,903
Maybe I'm the only one to think we're close.

613
00:38:41,729 --> 00:38:43,118
Why are you so upset?

614
00:38:45,078 --> 00:38:47,123
I'm scared you would be a jerk to Tam.

615
00:38:48,117 --> 00:38:49,603
Like how you did to other girls.

616
00:38:50,797 --> 00:38:51,711
Hey.

617
00:38:52,979 --> 00:38:53,711
You see?

618
00:38:54,102 --> 00:38:56,708
In the end, the one who couldn't move on is you.

619
00:39:00,849 --> 00:39:03,505
You judge and think I'm a jerk just like how the others look at me.

620
00:39:04,930 --> 00:39:05,705
Why?

621
00:39:05,880 --> 00:39:07,807
Do I not get any chance to redeem myself?

622
00:39:11,748 --> 00:39:13,120
Why does it have to be Tam?

623
00:39:13,729 --> 00:39:15,120
Because she likes me.

624
00:39:17,733 --> 00:39:18,902
And I like her.

625
00:39:19,918 --> 00:39:21,120
Perfect.

626
00:39:27,927 --> 00:39:30,106
So I wouldn't bother with your sister.

627
00:39:40,723 --> 00:39:42,609
But if you break Tam's heart this time,

628
00:39:46,371 --> 00:39:47,706
I'm not going to let it slide.

629
00:40:20,298 --> 00:40:21,909
Don't over-stress yourself.

630
00:40:22,018 --> 00:40:23,600
They're just starting.

631
00:40:25,981 --> 00:40:28,906
And also, you're the one who said it

632
00:40:29,333 --> 00:40:30,709
that you're going to keep yourself open.

633
00:40:35,521 --> 00:40:38,369
Kong, if you want to date someone,

634
00:40:42,960 --> 00:40:44,506
can I be one of your choices?

635
00:41:22,723 --> 00:41:24,809
I'm much kinder than you think.

636
00:41:38,261 --> 00:41:43,111
DIRECTED BY CHAINARONG TAMPONG

637
00:41:43,221 --> 00:41:46,609
Does everyone like someone like Pali?

638
00:41:47,280 --> 00:41:49,124
Someone fell for him?

639
00:41:49,274 --> 00:41:53,701
Can someone who loves himself so much really love someone else?

640
00:41:54,181 --> 00:41:55,484
If you want to go ahead,

641
00:41:55,518 --> 00:41:57,123
you should try giving him love first.

642
00:42:01,135 --> 00:42:02,311
Why are you so surprised?

643
00:42:10,160 --> 00:42:11,798
I don't like someone so mindful about skinship.

644
00:42:11,862 --> 00:42:14,542
Because I mind spending money when I have to.

645
00:42:14,564 --> 00:42:17,766
And now we're looking at my new car.

646
00:42:17,779 --> 00:42:18,717
He seems rich,

647
00:42:18,951 --> 00:42:20,503
but he really looks down on others.

648
00:42:21,058 --> 00:42:22,207
I miss you.

649
00:42:23,101 --> 00:42:24,604
What kind of person are you, Pali?

650
00:42:24,788 --> 00:42:26,038
How many people have you met?

651
00:42:26,478 --> 00:42:28,101
What the hell did you do?

652
00:42:30,338 --> 00:42:31,801
I screwed it up again.
